5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 248, L.D. 568, “An Act to Modify the
10 Process for Standard-offer Contracts with the Public Utilities Commission”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the Public Utilities Commission to Evaluate Different
13 Procurement Methods for Standard-offer Service'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Evaluation of standard-offer service procurement methods.
16 Resolved: That the Public Utilities Commission shall evaluate differing methods to
17 procure standard-offer service pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 35-A, section
18 3212, including, but not limited to, establishing supply contracts of varying lengths that
19 may include soliciting bids for the procurement of standard-offer service more frequently
20 than once per year. The commission shall consider methods to procure standard-offer
21 service that are likely to result in:
22 1. Improved bid quality and quantity;
23 2. Lower electricity rates for customers; and
24 3. Electricity rate stability.
25 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, no later than January 2, 2026, the Public Utilities
26 Commission shall submit to the Joint Standing Committee on Energy, Utilities and
27 Technology a report that:
28 1. Details the commission's evaluation under section 1;
29 2. Identifies whether the commission changed its procurement strategy for standard-
30 offer service beginning January 1, 2026 and whether any of the results identified in section
31 1 were achieved or are likely to be achieved;
32 3. Provides the commission's rationale if the commission did not change the
33 procurement strategy for standard-offer service beginning January 1, 2026; and
Page 1 - 132LR1665(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 248, L.D. 568
1 4. Includes other relevant information.
2 The committee may report out a bill related to the report to the Second Regular Session
3 of the 132nd Legislature.'
4 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
5 number to read consecutively.
6 SUMMARY
77 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. It requires the Public Utilities
88 Commission to evaluate differing methods to procure standard-offer service. It requires the
99 commission to consider methods that are likely to result in improved bid quality and
1100 quantity, lower electricity rates for customers and electricity rate stability. The commission
1111 is required to submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee on Energy, Utilities and
1122 Technology by January 2, 2026, and the committee is authorized to report out a bill to the
1133 Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
